{
  "text": "The above result does not hold, in general, for the \u2113-modular reduction of the Steinberg lattice of other classical groups, as no linear character a Sylow p-subgroup may be present in a given composition factor for such a group (cf. Example 5.4 of [CITATION_1] ).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "30312926"
